Step 2: Involve the Right People
 
List at least five employees or departments that should be involved. For each person or department, describe in 2–3 sentences what their role and responsibilities will be.

Departments
  - Human Resources - To help with implementing the security program for new hires as well as address violations.
    Human Resources will be responsible for obtaining and managing a signed security agreement for each employee.

  - Chief Executive Officer/Decision-Maker - The CEO is involved to ensure the security policy aligns with business goals.
    The CEO or Decision-Maker will be responsible for sharing the business roadmap with the Security team so they may stay aware of the possible attack methods             relevant to the business and create ways to protect.

  - Managers and Department Heads - All department managers/leaders are involved to better understand how each department accesses data and what risks are relevant to     their respective teams.
    Department Managers will be responsible for ensuring each of their team members complete the Security Assessments and obtain a passing score.
  - Managers are responsible for reporting any security breaches that occur within their departments.

